# Hugo Content Bundle Naming Convention Rules

## Overview

This document defines the standardized naming conventions for Hugo Content Bundles (Leaf Bundles) to ensure SEO optimization and maintainable content structure.

## Content Bundle Definition

A **Content Bundle** in Hugo is a folder containing an `index.md` file along with associated assets (images, documents, etc.). When creating new content bundles, strict naming conventions must be followed for optimal SEO and content organization.

### Types of Content Bundles
- **Leaf Bundle**: Contains `index.md` with no sub-pages (most common for blog posts)
- **Branch Bundle**: Contains `_index.md` with sub-pages (for sections)

## Folder Naming Convention

### Required Format
```
YYYY-MM-DD-title-with-keywords
```

### Format Breakdown
- **YYYY-MM-DD**: Publication date in ISO format
- **title-with-keywords**: SEO-optimized title with relevant keywords
- **Separator**: Use hyphens (-) between words
- **Length**: Keep folder name under 60 characters when possible

### Examples

#### Correct Examples
```
2025-08-06-thrustmaster-sol-r-2-hosas-space-sim-duo-review
2025-08-04-pyinstaller-python-executable-deployment-guide
2025-08-01-faststone-image-viewer-8-1-review
2025-07-30-chatgpt-study-mode-introduction
2025-07-29-windowing-techniques-stream-processing-data-analysis-guide
```

#### Incorrect Examples
```
thrustmaster-review (missing date)
2025-08-06_Thrustmaster_Review (wrong separators)
2025-8-6-thrustmaster-sol-r-2-hosas-space-sim-duo-review (inconsistent date format)
thrustmaster-sol-r-2-hosas-space-sim-duo-review-2025-08-06 (date at end)
```

## SEO Optimization Guidelines

### Title Selection Principles

#### **Keyword-Rich Titles**
- Include primary target keywords naturally
- Use long-tail keywords for better ranking
- Avoid keyword stuffing

#### **Descriptive and Specific**
- Be specific about the content topic
- Include product names, versions, or specific features
- Use action words when appropriate

#### **Length Considerations**
- Optimal length: 30-50 characters
- Maximum length: 60 characters
- Avoid overly short or generic titles

### SEO Best Practices

#### Recommended Patterns
```
{date}-{primary-keyword}-{secondary-keyword}-{specific-detail}
{date}-{product-name}-{version}-{review-type}
{date}-{topic}-{technique}-{application}
{date}-{software-name}-{feature}-{guide-type}
```

#### Keyword Strategy
- **Primary Keywords**: Main topic or product name
- **Secondary Keywords**: Related concepts or features
- **Long-tail Keywords**: Specific use cases or scenarios
- **Brand Names**: Include when reviewing or discussing specific products

## Directory Structure Rules

### Standard Structure
```
content/post/YYYY/YYYY-MM-DD-title-with-keywords/
├── index.md
├── featured-image.jpg
├── additional-image.png
└── supporting-document.pdf
```

## Implementation Guidelines

### Front Matter Alignment

#### Required Front Matter Fields
```yaml
---
title: "[Category] Human-Readable Title - Subtitle"
description: "SEO-optimized description (150-160 characters)"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
lastmod: YYYY-MM-DD
categories: 
- "Primary Category"
- "Secondary Category"
tags: 
- "primary-keyword"
- "secondary-keyword"
- "long-tail-keyword"
image: "featured-image.jpg"
---
```

#### Title Format Rules
- **Category Prefix**: Use appropriate category in brackets
- **Main Title**: Human-readable, SEO-optimized title
- **Subtitle**: Additional context or clarification
- **Length**: Keep total title under 70 characters
